# Coding Agents Pipeline

AI agent pipeline that turns PRDs into Pull Requests using AI coding agents (Claude Code or Gemini CLI), Ralph Loops, and Dev Containers.

## Structure

- `ca` — Unified CLI: wraps all pipeline scripts, always enables verbose logs and Dev Containers
- `scripts/install.sh` — curl-based installer for macOS and Linux
- `scripts/install-skills.sh` — Install Cursor skills locally
- `pipeline/orchestrator.sh` — Batch dispatcher: N PRDs × N repos, parallel execution
- `pipeline/run-pipeline.sh` — Single PRD × single repo: agent sequence, git, PR
- `pipeline/run-agent.sh` — Ralph Loop wrapper for one agent
- `pipeline/generate-context.sh` — Context skill generator: analyzes repos, produces context skills
- `pipeline/generate-prd.sh` — PRD and manifest generator: prompts for a description, uses repo contexts to produce PRDs and a manifest
- `pipeline/lib/` — Shared utilities (prd-parser, progress, git-utils, validation, provider)
- `agents/` — Agent prompt markdown files (`_base-system.md` + per-agent `prompt.md`)
- `templates/` — PRD, manifest, and context templates
- `skills/` — Cursor-compatible agent skills (SKILL.md format)
- `.devcontainer/` — Dev Container config (Dockerfile, firewall, post-create hooks)
- `config/` — AI CLI settings templates
- `.mcp.json` — MCP server configuration (GitHub, Notion, Figma, Slack)

## Pipeline Flow

```
Description → generate-prd.sh → PRDs + Manifest
N PRDs → orchestrator.sh → N×M work units → run-pipeline.sh → [Architect → Designer → Migration → Developer → Accessibility → Tester → Performance → SecOps → Dependency → Infrastructure → DevOps → Rollback → Documentation → Reviewer] → PRs
```

PRDs can be written manually or generated interactively using `generate-prd.sh`. The orchestrator dispatches one `run-pipeline.sh` per PRD×repo pair (parallel by default, max 4). Each agent runs in a Ralph Loop with filesystem-based progress tracking via `.agent-progress/*.md`.

## Key Files

- `ca` — unified CLI entry point (always verbose logs, always dev containers, `--follow` agent filtering)
- `agents/_base-system.md` — shared instructions inherited by ALL agents
- `pipeline/run-agent.sh` — Ralph Loop implementation (builds prompt, runs AI CLI, checks completion)
- `pipeline/lib/provider.sh` — AI provider abstraction (Claude Code / Gemini CLI)
- `pipeline/run-pipeline.sh` — sequences agents, manages git branches, creates PRs
- `pipeline/orchestrator.sh` — batch dispatcher, parses PRD metadata, parallel execution
- `pipeline/generate-prd.sh` — PRD and manifest generator (interactive prompt)
- `pipeline/generate-context.sh` — context skill generator from repo analysis
- `pipeline/lib/prd-parser.sh` — extracts repos, status, title from PRD markdown
